\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Citing Articles Instructions
\f1\b0\fs32 \cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 When citing articles in your project, use the following formats depending on the citation style required. Ensure each citation is complete and formatted correctly, including all relevant details such as authors, title, journal name, volume, issue, pages, and publication year.
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 1. APA Format
\f1\b0\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Format: Author(s). (Year). Title of the article. Journal Name, Volume(Issue), page range. DOI (if available).
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Example:
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Smith, J. A., & Brown, L. B. (2021). Organic compounds in artificial photosynthesis. Journal of Organic Chemistry, 86(3), 1245-1260.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://doi.org/10.1021/joc.0c12345"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 \ul \ulc5 \strokec5 https://doi.org/10.1021/joc.0c12345\cb1 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \ul \ulc5 Links to an external site.\cb1 \ulnone \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf4 2. ACS (American Chemical Society) Style
\f1\b0\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Format: Author(s). Title of the article. Journal Name Year, Volume, page range. DOI.
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Example:
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Green, M.; Blue, N. Advances in synthetic organic molecules. Chem. Rev. 2019, 119, 215-250. https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.chemrev.8b00569
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 3. MLA Format
\f1\b0\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Format: Author(s). \'93Title of the Article.\'94 Journal Name, vol. Volume, no. Issue, Year, pp. page range.
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Example:
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Johnson, Emma, and Lisa Wang. \'93Understanding Functional Groups in Organic Chemistry.\'94 Journal of Chemical Education, vol. 98, no. 2, 2020, pp. 123-132.
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 4. Chicago Style
\f1\b0\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Format: Author(s). \'93Title of the Article.\'94 Journal Name Volume, no. Issue (Year): page range. DOI.
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Example:
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 Taylor, Henry. \'93Applications of Organic Compounds in Pharmaceuticals.\'94 Science and Medicine 45, no. 6 (2022): 234-248. https://doi.org/10.1016/scimed.2022.0045
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

