\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Plagiarism and Academic Integrity
\f1\b0\fs43\fsmilli21600 \cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs37\fsmilli18667 \cf4 For this project, students are encouraged to discuss ideas and concepts with their peers, but all work submitted must be individually prepared (or jointly prepared if working in pairs). This means you must not copy any material, answers, or conclusions directly from another student\'92s project.
\fs32 \

\fs37\fsmilli18667 If you use any information, data, or phrasing from a website, article, or other external source, it must be properly cited. Failure to cite external sources will be considered plagiarism. Any project that is found to be copied, either partially or fully, from another student\'92s work will result in a zero for both parties involved.
\fs32 \

\fs37\fsmilli18667 Please take care to ensure your work reflects your understanding and effort. Academic integrity is a core value, and adherence to these guidelines will help you succeed and maintain a fair learning environment for everyone.
\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

